<br>
I founded the Twilight Bastion with the hope it could provide a good home to everyone who wanted to find one within its halls, despite the obstacles they face.  Unfortunately, as only one of those folks is around in the &quot;opposite hours&quot;, I'm afraid that the time-obstacle isn't being overcome very well.<br>
<br>
So, any of you &quot;down unders&quot;, or anyone else for that matter, looking for a home?  I realize the Bastion isn't for everyone, so lemme let you know what you will and won't find:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">What you Prolly Won't See</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
* At first, you prolly won't see many folks around in the off-times, unless we're all lucky<br>
* You won't have folks telling you who you can or can't associate with<br>
* You won't be told what to do or when to do it, and there are very few constraints on what you'd be told not to do <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(ooc: see our Guild Policies in the link from my sig-pic, they're pretty minor)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
* Overly-heated arguments or fights that do more harm than good, or similar dramatics that just plain hurt others<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">What you Prolly Will See</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
* People happy to see you, just cause of you being who you are<br>
* Jokies and stories, some of them even funny!<br>
* A true variety of backgrounds, personalities and goals, helping each other earn what we seek<br>
* A place where every voice can speak up to be heard, and openness and honesty is happily encouraged<br>
<br>
Well okays, there's a lot more to it than that, but I tried to list the basics!  So anyways, everyone have fun, and please drop by if you're curious about us.  You don't hafta join our guild for us to be happy to see you, and everyone who can behave themselves are more than welcome.<br>
<br>
